        <updateDate>2018-07-12T15:23:39Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>PLUS Loan Disability Forgiveness Act</b></p> <p>This bill amends the Higher Education Act of 1965 to require the Department of Education to forgive federal student loans under the Federal Family Education Loan Program for a parent of a student who: (1) becomes permanently and totally disabled, or (2) is unable to engage in substantial gainful activity by reason of a medically determinable physical or mental impairment that can be expected to result in death or that has lasted (or is expected to last) for a continuous period of no less than 60 months.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
